rComments: Really awesome instructor Considerate of students, doesn't require a textbook. Assigns a lot of dense readings (uploads pdfs) but is pretty lenient/ understanding with due dates. She is funny, entertaining and knowledgable. The class was very laid back but at the same, I learned a lot and the discussions in class everyday were interesting.

Dora is awesome! Extremely funny and makes students feel comfortable. Topic is a bit tedious, but she provides a lot of help when you approach her. She's there to see students succeed. I highly recommend taking her class.
good teacher, sympathetic with the amount of work that is required in writing 2. willing to share her personal stories to make class more interesting.

Dora is a grad. student who is currently teaching Writing 2: The Structure of Arguement. She is very funny and class is for the most part enjoyable even if it tends to last too long. Her comments on my writing didn't particularly help, but our required readings did. An interesting approach to language and arguement.
